OL,3,CRe-offending rates fall in Guernsey
OL,5,FRe-offending rates in Guernsey have
OL,6,Ffallen.
OL,8,FNew data shows that 12 out of 77
OL,9,Fpeople were reconvicted in 2023 within
OL,10,Ftwo years of being released.
OL,12,FFive years prior in 2018, just under a
OL,13,Fquarter would re-offend in that time
OL,14,F(28 out of 117).
OL,16,FOnly 7% of adults with a prison
OL,17,Fsentence and post-custody supervision
OL,18,Freoffended within two years by 2023.
OL,19,FOnce again, a fall from pervious years
OL,20,F- where in 2018 that figure was 24.5%.
